    <div class="formTitle">Cross-site Request Forgery Protection</div>
    Cross-site request forgery, also known as a one-click attack or session riding 
    and abbreviated as CSRF or XSRF, is a type of malicious exploit of a website 
    whereby unauthorized commands are transmitted from a user that the website trusts.
    <p style="font-weight:bold;">Note: The Aurora System is CSRF / XSRF protected by default.
    There is no configuration needed for this protection. This section serves as an awareness
    only and may include settings in future.</p>
